---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer vs Squarespace: Which Builder is Better in 2025?',
  description: 'Framer is faster and more modern for landing pages. Squarespace is better for e-commerce and content sites. Framer $16+/mo, Squarespace $23+/mo. Side-by-side comparison.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer vs Squarespace', 'website builder comparison', 'Framer review', 'Squarespace review', 'best website builder'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0099FF]/5 to-[#E07A5F]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0099FF] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builder Comparison · 2025 Updated
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer vs Squarespace
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Framer and Squarespace are both visual website builders but they target different users. Framer is faster, more modern, and better for designers who want pixel-perfect control. Squarespace is more established, better for e-commerce, and easier for complete beginners. Framer is the modern choice. Squarespace is the safe choice.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Framer if you care about modern design, animation, and speed. Choose Squarespace if you want built-in e-commerce, blogging, and don't mind templates that look more "traditional." Framer starts at $16/month. Squarespace starts at $23/month. Framer is faster to build with. Squarespace is more complete out of the box.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- At a Glance -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Framer vs Squarespace At a Glance
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold"></th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Squarespace</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4">Designers, portfolios, landing pages</td>
            <td class="p-4">Small businesses, e-commerce, blogs</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ease of use</td>
            <td class="p-4">Very easy (drag-and-drop)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Very easy (template-based)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design quality</td>
            <td class="p-14">Modern, beautiful</td>
            <td class="p-14">Polished, but feels dated</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Starting price</td>
            <td class="p-14">$16/month (Pro)</td>
            <td class="p-14">$23/month (Personal)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (via Stripe)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (built-in, powerful)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Blogging</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (CMS built-in)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (native, mature)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Templates</td>
            <td class="p-14">Many (modern)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Many (traditional style)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Custom domains</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (Pro+)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (all paid plans)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framer Overview -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer Does Best
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Modern Design System</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer is built for modern web design:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Beautiful templates:</strong> Current design trends, not stuck in 2015</li>
          <li>• <strong>Animation tools:</strong> Smooth micro-interactions built-in</li>
          <li>• <strong>Typography:</strong> Excellent font handling and responsive text</li>
          <li>• <strong>Pixel-perfect:</strong> Precise control over every element</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Designers who care about aesthetics and modern patterns.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Speed and Workflow</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer is incredibly fast to build with:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Visual editing:</strong> Drag-and-drop with smart snapping</li>
          <li>• <strong>Real-time preview:</strong> See changes instantly</li>
          <li>• <strong>Copy-paste styles:</strong> Quick design iteration</li>
          <li>• <strong>Component library:</strong> Reusable elements save time</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who want to design and launch quickly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. Built-in CMS</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer has content management:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Blog CMS:</strong> Native blogging with collections</li>
          <li>• <strong>Dynamic pages:</strong> Generate pages from content</li>
          <li>• <strong>Easy editing:</strong> Write content like a document</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Content creators who need blog or portfolio management.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. Code Export</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Unique among builders:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Export to React:</strong> Get actual code you can use</li>
          <li>• <strong>Developer-friendly:</strong> Clean, semantic output</li>
          <li>• <strong>Not locked in:</strong> Can host elsewhere</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Developers who want visual design with code freedom.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Squarespace Overview -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Squarespace Does Best
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Complete E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace has serious online store features:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Product management:</strong> Inventory, variants, digital products</li>
          <li>• <strong>Payment options:</strong> Multiple gateways built-in</li>
          <li>• <strong>Shipping:</strong> Real-time rates, labels, tax calculation</li>
          <li>• <strong>Marketing:</strong> Abandoned cart, promotions, email campaigns</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Online stores that need full e-commerce functionality.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Mature Blogging Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace started as a blog platform:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Rich blogging features:</strong> Categories, tags, comments, RSS</li>
          <li>• <strong>Author profiles:</strong> Multiple writers with bylines</li>
          <li>• <strong>Content scheduling:</strong> Plan and schedule posts</li>
          <li>• <strong>SEO built-in:</strong> Meta tags, sitemaps, structured data</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> Content-heavy sites and bloggers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. All-in-One Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace includes everything:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Hosting included:</strong> No setup required</li>
          <li>• <strong>SSL certificates:</strong> Security built-in</li>
          <li>• <strong>Domain registration:</strong> Buy through Squarespace</li>
          <li>• <strong>Email campaigns:</strong> Built-in email marketing</li>
          <li>• <strong>Analytics:</strong> Traffic insights and metrics</li>
          <li>• <strong>Scheduling:</strong> Booking for appointments</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who want one platform for everything.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. Established and Stable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace has been around since 2004:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Proven platform:</strong> Millions of sites live</li>
          <li>• <strong>Reliable uptime:</strong> Solid infrastructure</li>
          <li>• <strong>Support available:</strong> 24/7 chat and email</li>
          <li>• <strong>Template marketplace:</strong> Huge selection</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who value stability over cutting-edge features.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Use Cases -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Framer if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You care about modern, cutting-edge design</li>
          <li>• You're building portfolio or marketing site</li>
          <li>• You want animation and micro-interactions</li>
          <li>• You might want to export code later</li>
          <li>• You're comfortable with design tools</li>
          <li>• You want faster build workflow</li>
          <li>• You prefer newer, more modern interface</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Choose Squarespace if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You need serious e-commerce (inventory, shipping)</li>
          <li>• You're building a content-heavy blog</li>
          <li>• You want everything in one platform</li>
          <li>• You prefer established, proven platform</li>
          <li>• You want 24/7 support available</li>
          <li>• You don't care about having the newest design trends</li>
          <li>• You want built-in email marketing and scheduling</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feature Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Feature Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Squarespace</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design aesthetic</td>
            <td class="p-14">Modern, trendy</td>
            <td class="p-14">Polished, traditional</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Animation</td>
            <td class="p-14">Advanced micro-interactions</td>
            <td class="p-14">Basic transitions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="p-14">Via Stripe (basic)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Built-in (advanced)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Inventory management</td>
            <td class="p-14">No</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Shipping options</td>
            <td class="p-14">No</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (real-time rates)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Blog</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (CMS)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (native platform)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Code export</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (React)</td>
            <td class="p-14">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Email marketing</td>
            <td class="p-14">No</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (built-in)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Booking/scheduling</td>
            <td class="p-14">No</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (Acuity)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Starting price</td>
            <td class="p-14">$16/month</td>
            <td class="p-14">$23/month</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Free trial</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (14 days)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (14 days)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Framer Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Free:</strong> 2 sites, Framer branding</li>
          <li>• <strong>Pro ($16/month or $144/year):</strong> Custom domains, CMS, analytics</li>
          <li>• <strong>Basic ($25/month or $228/year):</strong> Everything in Pro + SEO features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Professional ($35/month or $324/year):</strong> Everything + team features</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Value:</strong> Good for marketing sites. E-commerce requires Stripe integration.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-2 border-orange-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Squarespace Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Personal ($23/month or $16/month billed annually):</strong> Basic website</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business ($33/month or $23/month billed annually):</strong> Business features, marketing</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce ($36/month or $27/month billed annually):</strong> E-commerce basic</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce Plus ($65/month or $49/month billed annually):</strong> Advanced e-commerce</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Value:</strong> Higher but includes more features (email, scheduling, full e-commerce).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Framer and Squarespace serve different needs despite overlapping features.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Framer if you want:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Modern design that looks current and fresh</li>
        <li>• Portfolio or marketing site (not e-commerce)</li>
        <li>• Animation and micro-interactions</li>
        <li>• Option to export code later</li>
        <li>• Faster, more modern workflow</li>
        <li>• Lower price point ($16 vs $23)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Squarespace if you want:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Serious e-commerce with inventory and shipping</li>
        <li>• Content-heavy blog with mature features</li>
        <li>• Everything in one platform (email, scheduling, analytics)</li>
        <li>• Established, proven platform with support</li>
        <li>• Traditional, polished design aesthetic</li>
        <li>• Not interested in cutting-edge features</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Try both:</strong> Both have 14-day free trials. Build a test page on each. See which interface you prefer. Framer feels newer and faster. Squarespace feels more complete and stable.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-vs-webflow" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Webflow</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Modern builders compared</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/framer-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Design vs AI generation</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
